<includeonly>{{#show:{{{page|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}}|?{{PAGENAME:{{{prop|}}}}}}}</includeonly><noinclude>
Returns a property's value on a page. Works uniformly for a regular page
or a subobject fragment (e.g. `MyBook#_abc123`).

This is a Tier A primitive — returns a plain string (empty if the page
has no value for the property) for use in custom display markup.

Accepts either a namespaced (`Property:Has_title`) or bare (`Has_title`)
property reference.

Parameters:
* prop - The property page reference
* page - The page or subobject fragment to read the value from; defaults
         to {{FULLPAGENAME}}

Example (regular page):
 {{Property/value|prop=Has_title|page=MyBook}}

Example (subobject fragment, typically inside a subobject-instances row template):
 {{Property/value|prop=Has_chapter_title|page={{{1}}}}}
</noinclude>
